components.name: Load Cleanup Configuration
components.description: Loads and validates cleanup configuration parameters from DAG run configuration and Airflow Variables, calculates the max_date used for retention.

components.name: Cleanup Airflow MetaDB
components.description: Deletes old entries from Airflow MetaStore tables based on the calculated max_date and configurable DATABASE_OBJECTS retention rules.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful execution of load_cleanup_configuration

connections.purpose: Access Airflow MetaStore tables via SQLAlchemy session

description.description: Comprehensive maintenance workflow that periodically cleans old metadata entries from Airflow's MetaStore database tables to prevent excessive data accumulation.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

max_db_entry_age_in_days.description: Maximum age of database entries in days, sourced from DAG run configuration or Airflow Variable 'airflow_db_cleanup__max_db_entry_age_in_days'.

provide_context.description: Flag to provide Airflow context to the Python callable.

DATABASE_OBJECTS.description: List of database objects and their retention rules to be cleaned.

ENABLE_DELETE.description: Flag to enable actual deletions; when false, performs a dryrun.

ALERT_EMAIL_ADDRESSES.description: Commaseparated email addresses to receive alerts on task failures.

sources: DAG run configuration parameters supplied at execution time
Existing rows in Airflow MetaStore tables (DagRun, TaskInstance, Log, XCom, etc.)
sinks: Deleted rows from Airflow MetaStore tables after cleanup
Failure notification emails sent via SMTP
intermediate_datasets: Inmemory Python objects representing DATABASE_OBJECTS configuration
